+# Task Queue System Implementation Plan
+
+> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use conclave:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.
+
+**Goal:** Build a fully-featured in-memory task queue system that supports 12 phases of increasing sophistication, from basic FIFO to graceful shutdown.
+
+**Architecture:** A central `TaskQueueSystem` class manages named queues, each represented by a `Queue` object containing tasks. All state is in-memory. Tasks move through statuses: `pending → processing → completed|failed|cancelled`. Features are layered incrementally — each phase builds on the prior without breaking backward compatibility.
+
+**Tech Stack:** TypeScript (strict mode), Node.js ESM, Vitest for tests, no runtime dependencies.
+
+---
+
+## File Layout
+
+```
+src/
+  types.ts          # All shared types/interfaces
+  Task.ts           # Task class
+  Queue.ts          # Queue class (manages tasks, concurrency, middleware)
